    "We make a testsuite 𝑇 available to AutoCodeRover, in addition to the problem statement 𝑃 and codebase 𝐶.Spectrum-based Fault Localization.",
    "The goal of SBFL is to identify the location of software faults [45].",
    "Given a test-suite 𝑇 containing both passing and failing tests, SBFL considers control-flow differences in the passing and failing test executions, and assigns a suspiciousness score to different program locations.",
    "This suspiciousness score can be computed with various metrics such as Tarantula [21] and Ochiai [3].",
